description:
Under certain circumstances, the code assist feature in the program is eating too much code. For example, in the given class, to make the program correct, a parameter needs to be added to the 'baz' call in 'bar'. However, when using code assist, it is adding too much code instead of just the necessary parameter. The code is changed to:

```java
void bar(X x) {
    baz(x.foo().foo());
}

int foo() {
    return 5;
}

void baz(int i, int j) {
}
```

This is not the expected behavior. The expected behavior is that code assist should only add the necessary parameter to the 'baz' call, like this:

```java
void bar(X x) {
    baz(x.x.foo());
}
```

OB:
The code is changed to:

```java
void bar(X x) {
    baz(x.foo().foo());
}
```

EB:
The code should be changed to:

```java
void bar(X x) {
    baz(x.x.foo());
}
```
